<paragraph blockId="9.[227,1436,1434,1612]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
The male of 
<taxonomicName box="[368,491,1480,1506]" class="Arachnida" family="Zodariidae" genus="Ballomma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="haddadi">
<emphasis box="[368,491,1480,1506]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">B. haddadi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
gen. et sp. nov. is easily recognized by the peculiar palp with the long, thin, sinuous embolus provided at its base with a large, sharp process pointing forward. The female has a characteristic epigyne with dark central area from where procurved cul-de-sac tubes originate, followed by well-separated spermathecae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="10" type="etymology">
