<collectionCode box="[488,508,306,332]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">B</collectionCode>
, 8 
<collectionCode box="[542,563,305,331]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">A</collectionCode>
– 
<collectionCode box="[578,598,306,332]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">B</collectionCode>
). Patella with pro- and retrolateral hair tufts. tibia with dorsolateral apophysis, roughly triangular and pointed, retrolaterally concave; cymbium with basolateral slightly indented protrusion, seven distolateral spines; tegulum high, in the middle with retrolateral protrusion with rounded tip; distally with membranous part ending in long, sickle-shaped apophysis (could be homologous to 
<collectionCode box="[407,459,446,472]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">MA</collectionCode>
); embolus originating on posterior part of tegulum, thin, slender, curved over central part of tegulum, with large sickle-shaped sclerite at base.
</paragraph>
