<figureCitation box="[235,309,441,468]" captionStart="Fig. 6" captionStartId="10.[227,270,1966,1992]" captionTargetBox="[245,1418,755,1933]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[245,1418,755,1934]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Fig. 6. Ballomma haddadi gen. et sp. nov. A – B. Holotype, ♂. C – F. ♀ (MRAC 132641). A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. As preceding, ventral view. C. Habitus, dorsal view. D. As preceding, ventral view. E. Prosoma, frontal view. F. Prosoma, dorsolateral view. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3471690" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3471690/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
<collectionCode box="[308,329,441,468]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">C</collectionCode>
– 
<collectionCode box="[346,369,441,468]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">D</collectionCode>
): dorsum and sides grey with complex dark pattern; venter pale with faint grey pattern, spinnerets pale yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[227,1436,541,603]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">CARAPACE. Smooth. Clypeus with dispersed setae. Chilum double, each sclerite 0.07 high, 0.10 wide; no setae. Sternum shield-shaped, 1.28 long, 1.14 wide.</paragraph>
